<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 2:31PM CDT  by NWS Austin-San Antonio</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Medina
and south central Bandera Counties through 315 PM CDT...
At 231 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hill Country State Natural Area, or near Tarpley, moving southwest at
10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Tarpley and Hill Country State Natural Area.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
